The evolution of gear can unlock greater effectiveness for the end-user. While skill still beats gear, it's undeniable that gear still matters a lot. Skill > Gear. It’s something we’ve been saying for years. So when it comes to getting the latest and greatest Sidecar holster… no you don’t absolutely have to upgrade. The Legacy Sidecar still gets you from point A to B. We know that’s not going to stop you from getting that new-new, but it’s important to remember that skill still beats gear. Focus on what matters most.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #sidecar #holster

This release also marks the launch of our new Training page, complete with a video archive of previous training videos, printable targets, drills, weapon and gear loadouts, and more.
And we're still just getting started...

Taking one class a year and using it to gather homework that you can use to improve on your own time is way more valuable than taking class after class after class and never really improving that much. Over the years, we have stressed the importance of personal education followed up with hard work and consistent practice. Eventually though, we all run into the problem of plateauing and that's where classes come in.
-
This year Lucas took a private class with @Joel.Park_ of @Practicalshootingtraininggroup and collected a lot of things he can be working on, which is what you're seeing here.
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

Candela is the measurement of directional light and is often a better way to determine what a flashlight is actually doing. High candela creates focused hot spots like on the @modlitesystems OKW and are very blinding and push light a really long way. When working inside though, that hot center can create a lot of shadows at whatever you are not lighting up. Options like the @surefire_llc M600 are often more flexible inside because of the "flood" of light that it throws. Though there are several great options for weapon lights on the market (Modlite, Surefire, Streamlight) finding what will work best given the environments you commonly find yourself in is crucial.

node.text:
Intuition and common sense needs to be applied to all aspects of guns. Yes, this even extends to setting up your gun. If you can't activate your light, shoot well with the light on or, turn the light off efficiently, then you may need to rethink the build. 
-
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by T.REX ARMS on September 17, 2021.

node.text:
Radian Raptor charging handles find their way onto just about every AR and MCX build in our armory. Hands down they're a best-in-class product, making manipulation of rifles significantly easier and more efficient.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by T.REX ARMS on September 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
Anyone can spend money. Not everyone can use their purchases to their fullest potential. Be the person who spends wisely and can use what they have proficiently. ⁠
-⁠
While this industry talks about pOoRs and Gucci crowds, there is usually a balance. Some people will spend big money on their gear but only acquire a percentage of the needed ability. Others will buy the cheapest stuff, train with it but never reach for the next level of kit. Yes, ability matters most, but good gear does too.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by T.REX ARMS on September 16, 2021. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
Your eyes should be the hardest working part of your body when you're shooting. Focus and see fast, but don't get tunnel vision. That's what really takes practice. Some sighting systems can help our eyes work as designed better than others. Brighter front sights or even better... red dots.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by T.REX ARMS on September 15, 2021.

node.text:
One of the best things about the AC1 design is its ability to receive other components. If you want to add side plates, thicker shoulder pads or drop pouches, its ready to rock. This AC1 has a Crye Precision cummerbund and Spiritus Sack attached. The placard for mags is made by Esstac, and is on our website. ⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #highstandards

node.text:
LMT 12.5” with an ACOG and offset Delta Point Pro. A set up like this may not look new or on the cutting edge of our industry, but items like this have been around for a long time and are still in use. Pay attention to products that have lasted more then ten years of real use. That's a track record to prove quality.⁠
-⁠
#trexarms #trexarmskydex #lmt #acog #cpc #crye

Adding armor does not change how you run your gun. Safety, trigger, loading the gun etc. will still have the same steps. Don't fall into the trap of thinking that you will be just as fast or consistent when you wear plates though. Depending on your body type, plate size and stock design, the stock may need to be positioned differently and you will have more gear to work around. All this being said, make sure you get some reps with the gear you have even if its dryfire.⁠

node.text:
If you're hitting up an Airsoft or other training event, be sure to run your gear as close as possible to how your rifle/kit is set up in "real life". The whole point is to test yourself and your gear, so taking shortcuts by removing your plates or lightening your loadout pretty much defeats the purpose. This goes for how you run your gear as well, as it would be easier/faster to shoot an airsoft gun without aiming down your optic, but you'd be losing out on getting reps and seeing through your optic and how it performs in different lighting and environments. Don't game it, even though it's a game. Hold yourself to a higher standard.⁠
-⁠
Drew with a modified AC1 + Mayflower Rig at Copperhead / Playas Training Center. ⁠
